The IDEXX SNAP 3Dx, SNAP 4Dx and SNAP 4Dx Plus products are examples of the multi-analyte capability of the SNAP test. These combination assays provide simultaneous detection of D. immitis antigen and antibody to either two (SNAP 3Dx), three (SNAP 4Dx), or five (SNAP 4Dx Plus) tick-borne pathogens in canine serum, plasma, or whole blood (Table 2
, Fig. 2
). Note that for the SNAP 4Dx Plus test, reagents for detection of antibodies to the Anaplasma species (phagocytophilum and platys) and the Ehrlichia species (canis and ewingii) are deposited in two genus-specific spots. Sensitivity and specificity for D. immitis antigen are similar to the SNAP Canine Heartworm test (Chandrashekar et al., 2010).
